OL,3,CMan dies days after being sent home
OL,4,Cfrom A&E with Gaviscon
OL,6,FHis partner, Sandra O'Hagan, from Sale
OL,7,Fin Greater Manchester, took him to
OL,8,FWythenshawe Hospital on 25 April,
OL,9,Fwhere he was diagnosed with gastritis
OL,10,Frather than an aortic dissection.
OL,12,FBut, he died just 15 days later.
OL,14,FSandra believes David would have had a
OL,15,Fsignificantly better chance of
OL,16,Fsurvival - and may even have still
OL,17,Fbeen alive - had he been correctly
OL,18,Fdiagnosed during his first A&E visit.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
